1
00:00:34,617 --> 00:00:37,954
UNDERCOVER MISS HONG

2
00:00:38,038 --> 00:00:40,707
PRESIDENT KANG NORA'S
NEW YEAR PRESS CONFERENCE

3
00:00:40,790 --> 00:00:44,044
Hello, I'm Kang Nora, the president
of Hanmin Investment &amp; Securities.

4
00:00:44,127 --> 00:00:45,545
Before I became president,

5
00:00:45,628 --> 00:00:50,008
I joined Hanmin on September 1, 1997,
as an entry-level employee,

6
00:00:50,091 --> 00:00:53,011
under my childhood name of Kang Eun-joo.

7
00:00:53,094 --> 00:00:57,098
Chairman Kang Pil-beom wished for me
to start at the bottom

8
00:00:57,182 --> 00:01:00,101
and learn alongside ordinary people.

9
00:01:00,185 --> 00:01:01,478
Well done, sir.

10
00:01:02,479 --> 00:01:04,522
That's also when I left home

11
00:01:04,606 --> 00:01:07,817
and moved into the Seoul City Dormitory
for Single Female Workers

12
00:01:07,901 --> 00:01:09,944
to live with roommates for three months.

13
00:01:11,821 --> 00:01:15,825
That was when I learned family is about
sharing meals, laughing together,

14
00:01:15,909 --> 00:01:17,202
and even arguing at times.

15
00:01:17,786 --> 00:01:22,040
I consider every Hanmin employee
a member of my family.

16
00:01:45,730 --> 00:01:48,274
Mom, I need to talk to Ms. Hong
briefly before we go.

17
00:01:49,901 --> 00:01:51,152
Okay.

18
00:01:56,533 --> 00:01:58,118
Bom, go see what Grandma is up to.

19
00:01:58,201 --> 00:01:59,035
Okay.

20
00:02:04,165 --> 00:02:05,416
I want to help too.

21
00:02:06,501 --> 00:02:08,044
I can do it too.

22
00:02:10,213 --> 00:02:11,756
You once told us

23
00:02:12,924 --> 00:02:16,845
that we have no idea how distrustful
and terrifying your father can be.

24
00:02:19,389 --> 00:02:21,516
We need someone who can stay by his side

25
00:02:21,599 --> 00:02:23,434
and deceive him until the very end.

26
00:02:24,644 --> 00:02:26,020
Do you think you can do that?

27
00:02:36,739 --> 00:02:37,699
Hello?

28
00:02:37,782 --> 00:02:39,450
<i>Your outfit for the press conference</i>

29
00:02:39,534 --> 00:02:41,494
<i>is in the women's locker room.</i>

30
00:03:21,910 --> 00:03:23,661
KANG EUN-JOO

31
00:03:31,336 --> 00:03:33,338
This is my favorite hairpin.

32
00:03:34,756 --> 00:03:37,926
This is a secret,
but wearing it gives you strength.

33
00:03:39,135 --> 00:03:41,054
For the sake of Hanmin

34
00:03:41,137 --> 00:03:43,431
and for the sake of the Hanmin family,

35
00:03:44,057 --> 00:03:47,644
I will exercise my shareholder rights
in support of Yeouido Pirates.

36
00:03:47,727 --> 00:03:49,896
What's this now?

37
00:03:53,650 --> 00:03:55,151
Ms. Song!

38
00:03:56,527 --> 00:03:57,654
And I know nothing

39
00:03:57,737 --> 00:04:00,073
about the Swiss borrowed-name account
in my name.

40
00:04:00,156 --> 00:04:01,824
Please reveal the truth,
National Tax Service!

41
00:04:07,747 --> 00:04:08,831
Get her!

42
00:04:11,042 --> 00:04:11,876
Why that little…

43
00:04:13,044 --> 00:04:14,462
Why, you brat!

44
00:04:18,091 --> 00:04:18,925
Get her!

45
00:04:19,008 --> 00:04:20,760
Damn it.

46
00:04:23,179 --> 00:04:24,389
Get her!

47
00:04:26,432 --> 00:04:30,144
HANMIN INVESTMENT &amp; SECURITIES

48
00:04:30,228 --> 00:04:32,855
EPISODE 16: WE OF THE NEW MILLENNIUM

49
00:04:39,070 --> 00:04:40,154
So

50
00:04:40,238 --> 00:04:43,574
Kang Nora just double-crossed
the chairman, right?

51
00:04:43,658 --> 00:04:44,534
Her own dad?

52
00:04:44,617 --> 00:04:47,036
But what was that
about a Swiss bank account?

53
00:04:47,120 --> 00:04:50,498
I hear there's 100 billion won
in that Swiss slush fund account.

54
00:04:50,581 --> 00:04:51,708
-One hundred billion won?
-Seriously?

55
00:04:53,251 --> 00:04:54,085
One hundred billion won?

56
00:04:55,461 --> 00:04:57,171
He had all that money…

57
00:04:59,257 --> 00:05:02,051
yet laid off workers,
saying the company was struggling?

58
00:05:04,595 --> 00:05:05,680
Damn it.

59
00:05:07,807 --> 00:05:09,225
I can't talk for long.

60
00:05:09,309 --> 00:05:11,686
It's all over the news right now.

61
00:05:11,769 --> 00:05:12,687
Hey,

62
00:05:13,479 --> 00:05:14,897
if it's all gone to hell,

63
00:05:14,981 --> 00:05:17,900
let's take what's ours while we can.

64
00:05:21,779 --> 00:05:24,157
<i>Hanmin's new year press conference today</i>

65
00:05:24,240 --> 00:05:26,701
<i>was anticipated to celebrate</i>
<i>the official transfer of power</i>

66
00:05:26,784 --> 00:05:30,872
<i>from Chairman Kang Pil-beom</i>
<i>to his only daughter, President Kang Nora.</i>

67
00:05:30,955 --> 00:05:32,040
<i>However, at the press conference,</i>

68
00:05:32,123 --> 00:05:34,125
<i>President Kang delivered</i>
<i>an unexpected announcement</i>

69
00:05:34,208 --> 00:05:36,586
<i>that left the room in shock.</i>

70
00:05:36,669 --> 00:05:40,214
<i>I will exercise my shareholder rights</i>
<i>in support of Yeouido Pirates.</i>

71
00:05:41,090 --> 00:05:44,093
<i>President Kang announced</i>
<i>that she would entrust her stake</i>

72
00:05:44,177 --> 00:05:46,429
<i>to Yeouido Pirates,</i>
<i>the second-largest shareholder</i>

73
00:05:46,512 --> 00:05:49,057
<i>which had demanded</i>
<i>the removal of Chairman Kang…</i>

74
00:05:52,894 --> 00:05:53,811
Sir.

75
00:05:55,646 --> 00:05:57,774
I think it'd be best for you
to go overseas for a while.

76
00:05:58,775 --> 00:06:02,278
I'm looking for the earliest flight
out of the country.

77
00:06:02,945 --> 00:06:04,072
I will gladly escort you.

78
00:06:04,155 --> 00:06:06,449
No, no.

79
00:06:06,532 --> 00:06:08,367
I'll need someone

80
00:06:08,451 --> 00:06:11,704
to stick around to deal with the press
and the police investigation.

81
00:06:12,246 --> 00:06:14,415
Who else can I trust?

82
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:18,461
The only people
who know about the slush funds

83
00:06:18,544 --> 00:06:21,130
are you and me.

84
00:06:21,214 --> 00:06:25,384
You should stay in Seoul
and take care of things for now.

85
00:06:25,468 --> 00:06:28,096
Afterward, we'll reconvene in Switzerland.

86
00:06:28,971 --> 00:06:32,600
I have to clear out
that Swiss account first.

87
00:06:32,683 --> 00:06:36,395
So before the police raid us,

88
00:06:36,479 --> 00:06:37,772
go to the office

89
00:06:38,356 --> 00:06:41,818
and get rid of anything
that could be incriminating.

90
00:06:45,780 --> 00:06:46,697
I have always…

91
00:06:49,367 --> 00:06:51,786
given it my all
for you and the company, sir.

92
00:06:53,538 --> 00:06:54,413
This time as well,

93
00:06:55,873 --> 00:06:58,543
I will follow your lead
without asking any questions.

94
00:06:59,168 --> 00:07:00,044
Good.

95
00:07:10,138 --> 00:07:12,140
I left my stuffed animals at my office.

96
00:07:12,223 --> 00:07:14,559
Should I ask the smug trio
to mail them to me?

97
00:07:14,642 --> 00:07:16,436
As if they'd ever do that for you.

98
00:07:16,519 --> 00:07:19,147
Come on, but I put on
such a passionate performance.

99
00:07:19,230 --> 00:07:21,941
Auntie, we all did it together.

100
00:07:23,651 --> 00:07:26,821
The police weren't charging her
with anything related to Hanmin.

101
00:07:38,082 --> 00:07:42,170
Ms. Go was suspected of embezzlement
and theft by her former employers

102
00:07:42,253 --> 00:07:44,964
before she even joined Hanmin.

103
00:07:45,047 --> 00:07:47,258
So are you saying it's my fault?

104
00:07:47,341 --> 00:07:50,052
You say whatever you want
and order everyone around.

105
00:07:50,136 --> 00:07:51,179
Why can't I?

106
00:07:55,850 --> 00:07:57,143
Auntie, what's wrong with you?

107
00:07:58,311 --> 00:08:00,021
I'm not like Albert.

108
00:08:00,646 --> 00:08:02,565
I don't want to be arrested
like Queen Bee.

109
00:08:09,447 --> 00:08:10,281
Ju-ran.

110
00:08:11,449 --> 00:08:12,617
It appears the soft-hearted Nora

111
00:08:13,117 --> 00:08:15,745
has turned on Yeouido Pirates.

112
00:08:16,954 --> 00:08:18,247
We had great teamwork.

113
00:08:19,332 --> 00:08:21,876
Chairman Kang and Ms. Song
let their guard down as a result.

114
00:08:23,503 --> 00:08:25,796
But they won't just stand by and watch.

115
00:08:27,006 --> 00:08:29,884
Someone keeps calling me,
and I'm pretty sure it's Ms. Song.

116
00:08:30,468 --> 00:08:31,719
Boy, she's scary.

117
00:08:33,888 --> 00:08:35,306
Where's President Kang?

118
00:08:35,389 --> 00:08:36,891
She hasn't come to work, has she?

119
00:08:36,974 --> 00:08:37,808
She's not picking up either?

120
00:08:37,892 --> 00:08:41,187
Ma'am, the NTS has requested cooperation
in a tax evasion investigation.

121
00:08:41,771 --> 00:08:45,107
Prosecutors have also issued
a summons in the slush fund probe.

122
00:08:47,777 --> 00:08:49,654
Don't respond to them
until there's a directive.

123
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:53,115
Ma'am.

124
00:08:54,158 --> 00:08:56,327
The police just requested
a witness interview.

125
00:08:56,410 --> 00:08:57,620
The police?

126
00:08:57,703 --> 00:09:01,040
They said the murder investigation
of Kim I-gyeong from the Songwi Branch

127
00:09:01,123 --> 00:09:02,458
has been reopened.

128
00:09:08,756 --> 00:09:14,303
CHAIRMAN KANG PIL-BEOM

129
00:09:34,448 --> 00:09:36,576
DOMESTIC POLITICIANS' SLUSH FUND LEDGER

130
00:09:38,828 --> 00:09:40,663
DOMESTIC POLITICIANS' SLUSH FUND LEDGER

131
00:09:41,247 --> 00:09:43,583
<i>Hey, if it's all gone to hell,</i>

132
00:09:43,666 --> 00:09:45,793
<i>let's take what's ours while we can.</i>

133
00:10:04,854 --> 00:10:06,272
It's Song Ju-ran.

134
00:10:06,355 --> 00:10:08,441
This is an urgent directive
from the chairman.

135
00:10:09,150 --> 00:10:09,984
How much cash

136
00:10:10,901 --> 00:10:12,236
do you have on hand?

137
00:10:19,535 --> 00:10:20,536
Ma'am.

138
00:10:20,620 --> 00:10:23,789
I've reserved two tickets
for a flight that leaves tonight.

139
00:10:23,873 --> 00:10:25,875
They're under
the chairman's name and yours.

140
00:10:25,958 --> 00:10:27,168
You can cancel one.

141
00:10:27,251 --> 00:10:29,962
The chairman won't be leaving.

142
00:10:51,192 --> 00:10:52,443
Where are you off to?

143
00:10:52,943 --> 00:10:54,487
To run an errand for the chairman.

144
00:10:55,112 --> 00:10:56,739
What are you doing here?

145
00:10:56,822 --> 00:10:59,158
I came to help you,

146
00:10:59,241 --> 00:11:00,868
just like how you protect the chairman.

147
00:11:02,078 --> 00:11:03,412
Let's go. I'll give you a ride.

148
00:11:04,497 --> 00:11:05,331
It's fine.

149
00:11:06,874 --> 00:11:08,626
You should lie low for a while.

150
00:11:09,502 --> 00:11:10,419
I'll be in touch.

151
00:11:13,130 --> 00:11:15,091
I said I'll give you a ride.

152
00:11:52,878 --> 00:11:54,922
It was just as you said.

153
00:11:57,133 --> 00:11:59,093
How do you know the chairman?

154
00:12:00,136 --> 00:12:01,637
Ms. Song.

155
00:12:02,847 --> 00:12:04,140
All this time,

156
00:12:04,223 --> 00:12:06,809
I'm sure you thought

157
00:12:07,476 --> 00:12:09,478
you were running the whole show

158
00:12:09,562 --> 00:12:13,524
as you relayed orders between him and me.

159
00:12:14,817 --> 00:12:15,818
But I…

160
00:12:17,153 --> 00:12:20,364
don't even trust my own flesh and blood.

161
00:12:21,365 --> 00:12:25,244
So how could I have

162
00:12:26,078 --> 00:12:27,997
trusted you alone…

163
00:12:29,748 --> 00:12:32,126
and vested you with full authority?

164
00:12:34,879 --> 00:12:35,880
I've devoted

165
00:12:37,339 --> 00:12:38,757
every fiber of my being

166
00:12:39,550 --> 00:12:41,177
to working for you and Hanmin.

167
00:12:42,303 --> 00:12:43,345
It has been

168
00:12:44,054 --> 00:12:45,764
thirty whole years.

169
00:12:49,018 --> 00:12:51,770
Even when he enticed me
to steal the slush fund together,

170
00:12:51,854 --> 00:12:53,731
I stayed by your side, sir.

171
00:12:54,982 --> 00:12:56,442
You must believe me.

172
00:12:57,359 --> 00:13:00,821
After stealing the company's reserve fund,

173
00:13:00,905 --> 00:13:03,324
she planned to leave
the country alone tonight.

174
00:13:04,366 --> 00:13:05,409
How dare you!

175
00:13:10,748 --> 00:13:12,625
Ms. Song Ju-ran.

176
00:13:16,170 --> 00:13:17,254
Thank you…

177
00:13:19,548 --> 00:13:21,258
for all your hard work over the years.

178
00:13:28,224 --> 00:13:29,099
Sir.

179
00:13:30,684 --> 00:13:31,727
Chairman.

180
00:13:32,728 --> 00:13:33,729
Sir!

181
00:13:36,065 --> 00:13:38,400
Chairman!

182
00:13:54,166 --> 00:13:56,210
The prosecution
has resumed its investigation

183
00:13:56,293 --> 00:13:58,254
into Hanmin's Chairman Kang Pil-beom.

184
00:13:58,337 --> 00:14:01,757
<i>The prosecution initially identified</i>
<i>Chief of Staff Song Ju-ran</i>

185
00:14:01,840 --> 00:14:03,717
<i>as a key figure</i>
<i>in the slush fund allegations,</i>

186
00:14:03,801 --> 00:14:06,887
<i>but the investigation has stalled,</i>
<i>with her whereabouts still unknown.</i>

187
00:14:06,971 --> 00:14:09,723
<i>Ms. Song was often referred to</i>
<i>as Chairman Kang's shadow</i>

188
00:14:09,807 --> 00:14:14,061
<i>and reportedly oversaw his secret accounts</i>
<i>at home and abroad.</i>

189
00:14:14,144 --> 00:14:15,104
SEOUL SOUTHERN DISTRICT COURT

190
00:14:15,187 --> 00:14:17,856
MARCH, 1998: FIRST TRIAL
FOR KANG'S SLUSH FUND EMBEZZLEMENT CASE

191
00:14:40,004 --> 00:14:42,172
Any lucky signs in your dream last night?

192
00:14:43,340 --> 00:14:44,758
I couldn't sleep a wink.

193
00:14:45,759 --> 00:14:48,220
It took way too long to get here.

194
00:14:48,304 --> 00:14:49,346
Gosh.

195
00:14:56,645 --> 00:14:57,730
Right,

196
00:14:58,314 --> 00:15:00,316
so if you really wanted
to go after Hanmin,

197
00:15:00,399 --> 00:15:03,652
you should've called me in
after securing concrete evidence.

198
00:15:09,408 --> 00:15:10,242
What's with him?

199
00:15:11,702 --> 00:15:14,371
We're lucky he was assigned this case.

200
00:15:15,414 --> 00:15:18,626
Not only was he jumped that night,
but he was also banished to Tongyeong.

201
00:15:18,709 --> 00:15:19,960
I hear that jerkface prosecutor

202
00:15:20,044 --> 00:15:23,631
also harbors a mighty grudge
against Chairman Kang.

203
00:15:23,714 --> 00:15:24,632
I see.

204
00:15:32,640 --> 00:15:35,976
Ms. Hong, please briefly explain
how this evidence

205
00:15:36,060 --> 00:15:37,603
came into your possession.

206
00:15:38,228 --> 00:15:40,856
While investigating Hanmin's slush fund,

207
00:15:40,940 --> 00:15:43,442
the late President Kang Myeong-hwi
reached out to me.

208
00:15:43,943 --> 00:15:46,612
He was supposed to hand over
the slush fund ledger,

209
00:15:47,821 --> 00:15:51,158
but he met his untimely death
in a questionable car accident,

210
00:15:51,241 --> 00:15:53,661
and the whistleblower
who compiled the ledger

211
00:15:53,744 --> 00:15:55,412
disappeared around that time.

212
00:15:56,288 --> 00:15:58,707
In order to find
the whistleblower and the ledger,

213
00:15:58,791 --> 00:16:00,417
I went undercover at Hanmin

214
00:16:00,501 --> 00:16:02,294
and carried out
an unofficial investigation.

215
00:16:02,378 --> 00:16:06,090
I acquired it through Ms. Go Bok-hee,
the late president's former assistant.

216
00:16:08,717 --> 00:16:09,551
That is all.

217
00:16:10,135 --> 00:16:11,011
The defense

218
00:16:11,595 --> 00:16:13,305
may begin questioning the witness.

219
00:16:22,690 --> 00:16:23,816
Ms. Hong,

220
00:16:24,400 --> 00:16:26,235
you were an inspector at the FSS

221
00:16:26,318 --> 00:16:28,612
when you took a job at Hanmin
under a false identity.

222
00:16:28,696 --> 00:16:29,989
Is that not an unlawful act?

223
00:16:30,072 --> 00:16:32,992
The undercover employment
was an inevitable step

224
00:16:33,075 --> 00:16:34,827
in continuing the slush fund probe.

225
00:16:34,910 --> 00:16:36,537
You claim it was a slush fund probe.

226
00:16:36,620 --> 00:16:40,541
Yet after you resigned,
you established "Yeouido Pirates,"

227
00:16:40,624 --> 00:16:44,169
an investment trust company,
to buy up Hanmin stocks, correct?

228
00:16:44,253 --> 00:16:45,295
Yes, that's correct.

229
00:16:45,379 --> 00:16:47,006
Was it to seize management control?

230
00:16:47,840 --> 00:16:50,092
It was to take part
in the company's management.

231
00:16:50,175 --> 00:16:54,013
I also wished to prevent the company
from a foreign acquisition.

232
00:16:54,096 --> 00:16:55,848
And where did you obtain the funds

233
00:16:55,931 --> 00:16:56,974
to purchase said shares?

234
00:16:59,810 --> 00:17:03,939
Shouldn't you be asking your client
about the source of those funds?

235
00:17:07,067 --> 00:17:09,361
That money was sourced from
Hanmin's slush fund

236
00:17:09,445 --> 00:17:11,655
recorded in the slush fund ledger.

237
00:17:11,739 --> 00:17:12,781
The slush fund?

238
00:17:22,332 --> 00:17:23,709
Your Honor.

239
00:17:23,792 --> 00:17:27,379
Ms. Hong was the party who initiated
Hanmin's management control dispute.

240
00:17:27,463 --> 00:17:29,965
Her claim that the money recorded
in the ledger was a slush fund

241
00:17:30,049 --> 00:17:32,176
is nothing more than a unilateral claim.

242
00:17:32,259 --> 00:17:34,970
More importantly, who exactly prepared

243
00:17:35,471 --> 00:17:37,431
the ledger in question?

244
00:17:47,357 --> 00:17:49,151
I will decline to answer that question

245
00:17:49,234 --> 00:17:51,028
to ensure the whistleblower's safety.

246
00:17:51,653 --> 00:17:54,990
So there's a ledger,
but we don't know who prepared it?

247
00:17:55,491 --> 00:17:57,826
Isn't it possible
that the ledger was fabricated

248
00:17:57,910 --> 00:18:00,913
to justify the hostile takeover
and to portray the funds

249
00:18:00,996 --> 00:18:02,664
as slush money?

250
00:18:02,748 --> 00:18:04,416
Could this be fabricated evidence?

251
00:18:04,500 --> 00:18:05,793
It is not.

252
00:18:07,127 --> 00:18:08,796
Let me be clear,

253
00:18:09,296 --> 00:18:12,591
I have no knowledge of any slush funds.

254
00:18:14,551 --> 00:18:18,722
I've never put together or even seen

255
00:18:18,806 --> 00:18:20,891
a slush fund ledger.

256
00:18:22,142 --> 00:18:26,897
Once the person who prepared
the mysterious ledger is identified,

257
00:18:26,980 --> 00:18:29,525
it will become clear as day

258
00:18:29,608 --> 00:18:33,195
who exactly is lying here.

259
00:18:37,199 --> 00:18:39,034
I, Kang Pil-beom…

260
00:18:41,120 --> 00:18:44,289
have only ever spoken the truth.

261
00:18:55,134 --> 00:18:57,052
We have something prepared,

262
00:18:57,136 --> 00:18:58,804
but we'll need some time.

263
00:19:07,604 --> 00:19:10,065
We'll take a 15-minute recess.

264
00:19:25,414 --> 00:19:27,082
Chairman Kang is doing that on purpose.

265
00:19:27,166 --> 00:19:28,709
He knows I can't speak up.

266
00:19:29,626 --> 00:19:31,837
Stop being so stubborn.

267
00:19:31,920 --> 00:19:33,005
Why can't you tell them?

268
00:19:33,088 --> 00:19:34,715
Just tell them who Yehppee is.

269
00:19:34,798 --> 00:19:37,426
Why do you refuse to identify them?

270
00:19:37,509 --> 00:19:40,220
I promised Yehppee
that I'd keep their secret.

271
00:19:40,804 --> 00:19:41,889
I can't break that promise.

272
00:19:41,972 --> 00:19:44,183
You're going to let this
slip through your fingers?

273
00:19:47,644 --> 00:19:49,938
Say something, President Shin.

274
00:19:50,522 --> 00:19:53,108
If you were just going to
sit there silently all day,

275
00:19:53,609 --> 00:19:55,694
you should've gone to a park
and sat on a bench.

276
00:19:56,278 --> 00:19:57,446
Go on.

277
00:19:58,238 --> 00:19:59,781
Who wrote the ledger?

278
00:19:59,865 --> 00:20:01,033
Can't you reach out to them?

279
00:20:01,116 --> 00:20:02,743
Yehppee ignores my calls.

280
00:20:03,577 --> 00:20:05,245
We got him hard evidence.

281
00:20:05,329 --> 00:20:08,624
We've set the stage well enough,
so it's up to the jerkface prosecutor now.

282
00:20:10,500 --> 00:20:11,335
Wait.

283
00:20:12,252 --> 00:20:14,796
Man, seriously? That's all you got?

284
00:20:14,880 --> 00:20:16,131
You are beyond frustrating.

285
00:20:16,215 --> 00:20:17,549
Wait, Hong!

286
00:20:18,425 --> 00:20:20,594
Am I the only one
who doesn't know who Yehppee is?

287
00:20:20,677 --> 00:20:21,762
I don't either.

288
00:20:22,262 --> 00:20:23,555
Me neither.

289
00:20:23,639 --> 00:20:24,473
"Yehppee"?

290
00:20:25,349 --> 00:20:27,142
So why was I the only one called out?

291
00:20:34,399 --> 00:20:35,317
Your Honor.

292
00:20:35,943 --> 00:20:38,403
I'd like to call an additional witness
to the stand.

293
00:20:39,780 --> 00:20:41,240
Why is this witness necessary?

294
00:20:42,032 --> 00:20:45,285
This witness's testimony is essential
to establishing the facts.

295
00:20:45,369 --> 00:20:48,580
Wouldn't that violate
the defendant's right to a defense?

296
00:20:48,664 --> 00:20:50,666
The defense had
also requested this witness.

297
00:20:50,749 --> 00:20:53,585
He is already in attendance
in the courtroom.

298
00:20:58,173 --> 00:20:59,258
Is it me?

299
00:20:59,841 --> 00:21:00,759
I don't think so.

300
00:21:00,842 --> 00:21:01,969
No, right?

301
00:21:02,052 --> 00:21:04,638
We'll allow the witness's examination
as an exception.

302
00:21:04,721 --> 00:21:06,431
However, please ensure
that defense counsel

303
00:21:06,515 --> 00:21:09,351
is given ample opportunity
for cross-examination.

304
00:21:09,434 --> 00:21:10,769
Yes, Your Honor.

305
00:21:10,852 --> 00:21:14,439
Formerly with Hanmin's head office
and author of the slush fund ledger,

306
00:21:14,523 --> 00:21:15,524
we call Mr. Bang Jin-mok.

307
00:22:25,802 --> 00:22:29,598
"I swear to tell the truth
and nothing but the truth,

308
00:22:29,681 --> 00:22:31,016
to testify truthfully,

309
00:22:31,099 --> 00:22:34,269
and conceal nothing,
in accordance with my conscience."

310
00:22:34,728 --> 00:22:36,563
"Witness, Bang Jin-mok."

311
00:22:39,900 --> 00:22:41,318
Mr. Bang.

312
00:22:42,152 --> 00:22:43,278
This ledger

313
00:22:43,904 --> 00:22:45,614
was written by you, correct?

314
00:22:45,697 --> 00:22:47,407
Yes, I did.

315
00:22:47,491 --> 00:22:48,909
For what purpose did you write it?

316
00:22:49,493 --> 00:22:51,453
At President Kang Myeong-hwi's urging,

317
00:22:52,120 --> 00:22:55,248
I documented it to condemn
Chairman Kang Pil-beom's slush fund

318
00:22:55,332 --> 00:22:57,334
and to ensure
a brighter future for Hanmin.

319
00:22:59,961 --> 00:23:01,713
Could President Kang Myeong-hwi

320
00:23:01,797 --> 00:23:05,092
have commissioned the ledger
in an effort to oust his father,

321
00:23:05,175 --> 00:23:07,677
Chairman Kang Pil-beom,
and take control of Hanmin?

322
00:23:08,887 --> 00:23:10,639
I do not believe so.

323
00:23:10,722 --> 00:23:12,516
That's your speculation.

324
00:23:14,184 --> 00:23:16,478
Aren't you speculating as well?

325
00:23:16,978 --> 00:23:18,563
The dead can't speak up.

326
00:23:20,565 --> 00:23:24,444
Was that ledger truly compiled
when President Kang Myeong-hwi was alive?

327
00:23:24,528 --> 00:23:27,781
Are you certain it wasn't fabricated
after the control dispute began?

328
00:23:28,365 --> 00:23:30,367
How can you prove that?
There's only one ledger--

329
00:23:30,450 --> 00:23:32,160
There isn't just one.

330
00:23:34,955 --> 00:23:35,997
There are 13 in total.

331
00:23:40,335 --> 00:23:41,461
Did he say 13?

332
00:23:44,631 --> 00:23:47,092
Hanmin was my first job,

333
00:23:47,175 --> 00:23:50,679
and my seniors taught me
the fundamentals of corporate life.

334
00:23:50,762 --> 00:23:53,223
"Doubt everything, verify everything,

335
00:23:53,306 --> 00:23:55,433
and always keep a backup."

336
00:23:55,517 --> 00:23:57,144
There were multiple backups?

337
00:23:58,395 --> 00:23:59,813
Twelve more, at that?

338
00:24:01,356 --> 00:24:03,984
I left the company last December
when the IMF crisis struck

339
00:24:04,067 --> 00:24:05,861
and restructuring began.

340
00:24:06,528 --> 00:24:10,073
My twelfth backup is hidden in the ceiling
of the Risk Management office

341
00:24:10,157 --> 00:24:13,243
at Hanmin's head office building,
where I used to work.

342
00:24:14,035 --> 00:24:15,871
What? Where?

343
00:24:22,002 --> 00:24:22,836
<i>Yehppee!</i>

344
00:24:27,591 --> 00:24:28,466
At the time,

345
00:24:29,509 --> 00:24:33,513
Yeouido Pirates had no involvement
in the management of Hanmin.

346
00:24:33,597 --> 00:24:35,974
And after my exit last December,

347
00:24:36,057 --> 00:24:38,268
I've never set foot in the head office.

348
00:24:49,571 --> 00:24:50,405
I was…

349
00:24:51,615 --> 00:24:52,616
very scared.

350
00:24:53,950 --> 00:24:55,243
There were even times

351
00:24:55,327 --> 00:24:58,663
when I regretted ever getting involved.

352
00:25:00,248 --> 00:25:01,082
However,

353
00:25:03,084 --> 00:25:05,795
I didn't want my courage

354
00:25:06,796 --> 00:25:07,631
and…

355
00:25:10,550 --> 00:25:11,551
the effort

356
00:25:13,053 --> 00:25:14,054
of my former colleagues

357
00:25:15,680 --> 00:25:19,517
to be forever in vain.

358
00:25:22,354 --> 00:25:25,565
Even if you claim
the ledger was fabricated…

359
00:25:27,776 --> 00:25:29,569
I can prove otherwise.

360
00:25:52,592 --> 00:25:53,885
Thanks.

361
00:25:57,764 --> 00:26:00,308
Is this why you refused
to return to the company?

362
00:26:00,392 --> 00:26:01,893
This needed to be settled first.

363
00:26:02,477 --> 00:26:04,479
So you're not entirely against going back?

364
00:26:04,562 --> 00:26:07,524
Why do you care?
You don't work for Hanmin anymore.

365
00:26:08,108 --> 00:26:12,279
Will Inspector Hong Keum-bo
be returning to the FSS now?

366
00:26:13,113 --> 00:26:14,781
Who says they'd even take me back?

367
00:26:15,740 --> 00:26:17,450
I bet they already cleared out your desk.

368
00:26:18,618 --> 00:26:22,247
With that ledger in your hand,
you stole all those slush funds.

369
00:26:22,330 --> 00:26:24,124
You have to take responsibility.

370
00:26:24,207 --> 00:26:26,501
I'm going to file a reinstatement lawsuit.

371
00:26:27,085 --> 00:26:30,588
I'll prove that the investigation
was related to my work, no matter what.

372
00:26:30,672 --> 00:26:32,841
You can't prove that by yourself.

373
00:26:35,218 --> 00:26:37,137
I wouldn't have gone through this trouble

374
00:26:37,220 --> 00:26:38,888
if Yehppee had been more cooperative.

375
00:26:43,518 --> 00:26:45,437
I'll cooperate this time.

376
00:26:46,271 --> 00:26:47,105
I promise.

377
00:26:50,025 --> 00:26:51,651
Call me if you ever need anything.

378
00:26:56,197 --> 00:26:58,491
There's a lot left here. You drink it.

379
00:26:59,659 --> 00:27:00,493
I'm off.

380
00:27:17,635 --> 00:27:19,095
Did you ask the investigative team?

381
00:27:19,679 --> 00:27:21,181
I asked discreetly,

382
00:27:22,265 --> 00:27:25,935
and they said Chairman Kang
is still denying all allegations.

383
00:27:26,019 --> 00:27:27,187
He claims he knows nothing,

384
00:27:27,687 --> 00:27:31,149
that it was all Song Ju-ran's doing
behind his back.

385
00:27:31,691 --> 00:27:34,486
That's nonsense.
He's just trying to pin it all on her.

386
00:27:34,569 --> 00:27:36,488
Of course, it's nonsense.

387
00:27:36,571 --> 00:27:41,159
That's why the investigative team
is scrambling to find Song Ju-ran.

388
00:27:41,242 --> 00:27:43,495
If she doesn't come out of hiding,

389
00:27:43,578 --> 00:27:46,164
it may be difficult to prove
Chairman Kang's charges.

390
00:27:46,831 --> 00:27:49,125
But there's no record
of her flying out of the country.

391
00:27:50,085 --> 00:27:51,628
That means she's still in the country.

392
00:27:52,796 --> 00:27:54,923
Or maybe she left by boat?

393
00:27:56,800 --> 00:28:00,470
Didn't Chairman Kang seem
a bit too calm during the trial?

394
00:28:01,054 --> 00:28:02,472
Like he had something up his sleeve?

395
00:28:02,555 --> 00:28:04,849
With even the politicians'
slush funds exposed,

396
00:28:04,933 --> 00:28:06,393
there's no one left to help him.

397
00:28:08,561 --> 00:28:10,897
Let's look at it
from Chairman Kang's perspective.

398
00:28:12,065 --> 00:28:15,693
Ms. Song was the only one
who knew every detail of his slush fund.

399
00:28:16,528 --> 00:28:19,489
If Ms. Song, who knows too much
about the slush fund, is gone…

400
00:28:20,740 --> 00:28:22,492
What if he could make her disappear?

401
00:28:22,575 --> 00:28:24,536
It would certainly raise suspicions,

402
00:28:24,619 --> 00:28:26,579
but he could avoid a guilty verdict?

403
00:28:31,084 --> 00:28:32,293
Damn bastard…

404
00:28:37,632 --> 00:28:40,468
HANMIN'S OUTSTANDING WOMEN EMPLOYEES

405
00:28:41,845 --> 00:28:44,222
WOMAN IN HER 20S FOUND DEAD
IN CHUNGSEO RESERVOIR

406
00:29:00,029 --> 00:29:01,573
Prosecutor, it's Hong Keum-bo.

407
00:29:02,782 --> 00:29:04,576
Do you want some help finding Song Ju-ran?

408
00:29:07,787 --> 00:29:08,663
Sir,

409
00:29:08,747 --> 00:29:12,041
DNA was found under the victim
Kim I-gyeong's fingernails.

410
00:29:12,125 --> 00:29:14,419
Once a suspect is identified,
we can run a DNA test--

411
00:29:14,502 --> 00:29:17,046
It's been almost three months
since the body was found,

412
00:29:17,130 --> 00:29:18,673
and we still don't have a suspect.

413
00:29:19,549 --> 00:29:21,509
Just rule it as a suicide already.

414
00:29:21,593 --> 00:29:22,969
But it wasn't a suicide!

415
00:29:24,262 --> 00:29:26,765
We have the plate number
of the van she got into.

416
00:29:26,848 --> 00:29:27,682
Bro.

417
00:29:27,766 --> 00:29:31,478
If she got into the back seat,
that means someone else was driving.

418
00:29:31,561 --> 00:29:34,856
That was a stolen plate, remember?

419
00:29:34,939 --> 00:29:37,192
Why are you being so stubborn about this?

420
00:29:37,275 --> 00:29:39,152
Man, you're so damn frustrating.

421
00:29:40,028 --> 00:29:41,738
-Wait, bro!
-Whatever. Leave me alone!

422
00:29:41,821 --> 00:29:42,947
We have work to do!

423
00:29:49,579 --> 00:29:50,413
Hello?

424
00:29:53,374 --> 00:29:54,292
Who is this?

425
00:29:55,668 --> 00:29:58,379
<i>There's a shop called Horang Auto Repair</i>
<i>on Seoul's outskirts.</i>

426
00:29:59,589 --> 00:30:02,717
<i>It's run by a man in his late forties</i>
<i>named Bong Dal-su.</i>

427
00:30:03,760 --> 00:30:05,637
<i>And according to a reliable source,</i>

428
00:30:05,720 --> 00:30:08,139
he's somehow related
to Kim I-gyeong's death.

429
00:30:08,223 --> 00:30:09,057
Sir.

430
00:30:12,519 --> 00:30:15,188
It matches the plate seen
on the day she disappeared.

431
00:30:16,439 --> 00:30:17,732
SEOUL 6
K 3307

432
00:30:19,609 --> 00:30:21,444
OFFICE

433
00:30:27,450 --> 00:30:29,869
This is the evidence we collected
from Horang Auto Repair Shop.

434
00:30:30,578 --> 00:30:32,580
It appears Bong Dal-su kept them

435
00:30:33,081 --> 00:30:34,499
as souvenirs of his crimes.

436
00:30:35,458 --> 00:30:36,960
Hanmin President Kang Myeong-hwi's wallet…

437
00:30:41,923 --> 00:30:44,300
and Songwi Branch teller
Kim I-gyeong's wallet were found.

438
00:30:44,884 --> 00:30:46,344
Aside from those two victims,

439
00:30:46,427 --> 00:30:49,097
the others don't appear
to be connected to Hanmin.

440
00:30:50,265 --> 00:30:51,224
Just a moment.

441
00:30:52,433 --> 00:30:53,852
Can I take a look at this?

442
00:30:53,935 --> 00:30:54,769
Sure.

443
00:31:06,573 --> 00:31:08,408
CHEONGSAN ACCOUNTING FIRM

444
00:31:10,368 --> 00:31:12,453
YUN JAE-UNG

445
00:31:12,537 --> 00:31:17,000
RESIDENT REGISTRATION CARD
YUN JAE-UNG

446
00:31:21,796 --> 00:31:23,131
<i>…and audit report wordplay.</i>

447
00:31:23,214 --> 00:31:24,215
HANMIN FINANCIAL AUDIT

448
00:31:24,299 --> 00:31:25,300
It's all unacceptable.

449
00:31:25,383 --> 00:31:27,010
-Mr. Yun.
-Yes, sir?

450
00:31:27,093 --> 00:31:28,261
<i>Sorry, Keum-bo.</i>

451
00:31:28,344 --> 00:31:31,389
I'll persuade him to do the right thing.

452
00:31:32,307 --> 00:31:35,143
<i>Mr. Yun, the accountant</i>
<i>who was being investigated by the police,</i>

453
00:31:35,226 --> 00:31:37,812
<i>committed suicide</i>
<i>by jumping from his apartment building</i>

454
00:31:37,896 --> 00:31:38,938
<i>around 3 p.m. today.</i>

455
00:31:51,576 --> 00:31:53,995
If Bong Dal-su doesn't show up today…

456
00:31:54,537 --> 00:31:56,998
Then we'll continue waiting tomorrow.

457
00:32:01,210 --> 00:32:02,295
He's on the wanted list.

458
00:32:02,378 --> 00:32:04,881
We appreciate the tip,
but it's our job to investigate--

459
00:32:04,964 --> 00:32:06,132
He's here. There.

460
00:32:35,620 --> 00:32:36,663
Go on. Follow him.

461
00:32:36,746 --> 00:32:38,414
-Maintain distance.
-Yes, ma'am.

462
00:32:38,498 --> 00:32:39,999
-Hurry up.
-Yes, sir.

463
00:33:04,816 --> 00:33:07,151
Wait, why is he going into that house?

464
00:33:07,235 --> 00:33:08,361
Do you recognize it?

465
00:33:08,444 --> 00:33:10,655
It's Chairman Kang Pil-beom's place.

466
00:33:11,155 --> 00:33:13,116
Hey, let's request a warrant first.

467
00:33:15,576 --> 00:33:17,245
I'll get off nearby.

468
00:33:17,829 --> 00:33:20,498
My goodness, you didn't need to.

469
00:33:21,666 --> 00:33:22,667
Ta-da.

470
00:33:27,630 --> 00:33:28,673
Ta-da!

471
00:33:28,756 --> 00:33:31,718
I heard you're supposed to eat tofu
when you get out of prison

472
00:33:31,801 --> 00:33:32,635
to purify your soul.

473
00:33:32,719 --> 00:33:34,470
I haven't gone to prison yet.

474
00:33:34,554 --> 00:33:36,431
I'm being investigated without detention.

475
00:33:37,015 --> 00:33:40,518
I guess I'll have a bite
since you went through the trouble.

476
00:33:41,894 --> 00:33:42,979
Is there no soy sauce?

477
00:33:43,813 --> 00:33:44,647
No.

478
00:33:48,818 --> 00:33:49,652
Hello?

479
00:33:50,236 --> 00:33:51,112
Nora,

480
00:33:51,654 --> 00:33:53,531
do you still have the keys
to Chairman Kang's house?

481
00:33:54,407 --> 00:33:55,241
Yes.

482
00:33:55,324 --> 00:33:56,826
Come meet me right now.

483
00:33:57,410 --> 00:33:58,536
What is it?

484
00:34:22,101 --> 00:34:24,145
The chairman has made a decision.

485
00:34:28,066 --> 00:34:29,692
I don't want to do this either.

486
00:34:31,986 --> 00:34:33,529
You understand, right?

487
00:34:45,583 --> 00:34:48,336
This is why you should've listened to me.

488
00:34:50,171 --> 00:34:51,714
I said we should just take the money.

489
00:34:56,427 --> 00:34:57,428
Damn it.

490
00:34:59,222 --> 00:35:00,348
The chairman has already

491
00:35:01,099 --> 00:35:02,642
left this palace of a house.

492
00:35:04,769 --> 00:35:05,686
The whole world is

493
00:35:06,395 --> 00:35:08,106
buzzing about the slush fund.

494
00:35:08,773 --> 00:35:10,817
No one will care if you disappear.

495
00:35:13,069 --> 00:35:15,196
People can be so cruel.

496
00:35:15,696 --> 00:35:16,531
Right?

497
00:35:22,203 --> 00:35:24,747
I'll be back
after I park the car in the garage.

498
00:35:58,239 --> 00:35:59,365
Let's get out of here.

499
00:36:04,078 --> 00:36:05,413
You can't die like this.

500
00:36:17,300 --> 00:36:18,134
Let's hurry.

501
00:36:37,486 --> 00:36:38,696
Now,

502
00:36:39,655 --> 00:36:41,908
none of you can make it out alive.

503
00:36:45,828 --> 00:36:46,954
Go and hide down there.

504
00:36:47,038 --> 00:36:48,873
-What about you?
-I'll be fine. Hurry.

505
00:36:50,499 --> 00:36:51,751
Let's go for now.

506
00:36:51,834 --> 00:36:52,668
Where are you going?

507
00:36:53,419 --> 00:36:54,462
Hey, stop.

508
00:36:55,004 --> 00:36:56,214
Why you little…

509
00:37:11,896 --> 00:37:12,772
Damn you.

510
00:37:22,323 --> 00:37:23,407
Damn it. Let go of me.

511
00:37:36,796 --> 00:37:37,630
Damn it.

512
00:37:41,300 --> 00:37:43,052
You're not going anywhere.

513
00:37:47,974 --> 00:37:48,933
What's your deal?

514
00:37:49,016 --> 00:37:51,060
Why? Tell me.

515
00:37:51,143 --> 00:37:52,561
Why?

516
00:37:52,645 --> 00:37:53,479
Damn it!

517
00:37:54,355 --> 00:37:55,189
You!

518
00:38:05,658 --> 00:38:06,617
Damn it.

519
00:38:31,100 --> 00:38:35,479
The unidentified DNA
found under Kim I-gyeong's fingernails…

520
00:38:39,150 --> 00:38:41,569
matches yours, Bong Dal-su.

521
00:38:43,529 --> 00:38:45,614
Did you keep those wallets in your drawer

522
00:38:45,698 --> 00:38:47,616
as souvenirs after you killed the victims?

523
00:38:48,159 --> 00:38:49,994
Then what about Hanmin President
Kang Myeong-hwi?

524
00:38:53,622 --> 00:38:56,083
You didn't do it alone.
You know Song Ju-ran, don't you?

525
00:38:56,876 --> 00:39:00,379
The Hanmin Chief of Staff you confined
in Chairman Kang's basement.

526
00:39:04,342 --> 00:39:05,217
Everything

527
00:39:05,801 --> 00:39:07,720
was under Song Ju-ran's orders.

528
00:39:10,097 --> 00:39:11,307
It's true.

529
00:39:15,227 --> 00:39:16,520
That's not true, is it?

530
00:39:16,604 --> 00:39:18,272
There's someone above her.

531
00:39:19,315 --> 00:39:20,566
Chairman Kang Pil-beom.

532
00:39:21,150 --> 00:39:22,068
Where is he?

533
00:39:48,010 --> 00:39:49,178
Why aren't you eating?

534
00:39:49,261 --> 00:39:52,390
You need to recover
so you can get investigated by the police

535
00:39:52,890 --> 00:39:54,642
and stand trial.

536
00:39:56,727 --> 00:39:58,104
Did you come all this way

537
00:39:59,271 --> 00:40:00,314
for a thank you?

538
00:40:02,566 --> 00:40:03,734
At the end of the day…

539
00:40:05,778 --> 00:40:07,696
you only found me to use me.

540
00:40:08,531 --> 00:40:10,533
You're half-right and half-wrong.

541
00:40:12,493 --> 00:40:15,663
I wanted you to be fairly judged
and punished accordingly.

542
00:40:16,372 --> 00:40:17,665
I never wanted you dead.

543
00:40:18,874 --> 00:40:20,209
It's not because it's you,

544
00:40:21,043 --> 00:40:22,753
but because nobody deserves that.

545
00:40:24,588 --> 00:40:27,716
For all the female employees
who admired you

546
00:40:28,259 --> 00:40:31,095
but were exploited and discarded by you…

547
00:40:33,180 --> 00:40:35,474
I hope you live with remorse
from this day on.

548
00:41:13,345 --> 00:41:16,390
<i>Ms. Song, the chief of staff at Hanmin</i>
<i>who covered up the murder</i>

549
00:41:16,474 --> 00:41:19,435
<i>of a female branch employee as a suicide,</i>
<i>has been arrested.</i>

550
00:41:19,518 --> 00:41:23,397
<i>After DNA found on the victim's body</i>
<i>matched that of Mr. Bong,</i>

551
00:41:23,481 --> 00:41:25,649
<i>an acquaintance of Ms. Song</i>
<i>from her hometown,</i>

552
00:41:25,733 --> 00:41:29,904
<i>the police reclassified the case</i>
<i>from suicide to homicide.</i>

553
00:41:29,987 --> 00:41:33,699
<i>Ms. Song had previously been identified</i>
<i>as a key figure</i>

554
00:41:33,782 --> 00:41:37,036
<i>and the so-called "key man"</i>
<i>in the Hanmin slush fund investigation.</i>

555
00:41:37,119 --> 00:41:39,205
So I'm banned from leaving the country

556
00:41:40,080 --> 00:41:42,583
starting at noon tomorrow?

557
00:41:42,666 --> 00:41:44,001
Not today, right?

558
00:41:45,628 --> 00:41:46,462
All right.

559
00:41:47,463 --> 00:41:48,756
I understand.

560
00:41:48,839 --> 00:41:51,383
Come visit me in Switzerland sometime.

561
00:41:52,510 --> 00:41:55,554
I'll make sure to repay you then.

562
00:41:56,180 --> 00:41:57,014
Good.

563
00:41:57,097 --> 00:41:58,307
Oh jeez.

564
00:41:58,390 --> 00:41:59,266
Chairman.

565
00:42:00,017 --> 00:42:01,560
Have you been hiding here this whole time?

566
00:42:02,937 --> 00:42:05,981
How did you even know about this place?

567
00:42:06,065 --> 00:42:07,775
I know you, honey.

568
00:42:08,275 --> 00:42:09,401
Even when we were together,

569
00:42:09,485 --> 00:42:12,071
you always came to this VIP ward
whenever things got tough.

570
00:42:14,031 --> 00:42:16,575
You saw the news
about Song Ju-ran's arrest, right?

571
00:42:17,326 --> 00:42:18,869
What did I tell you?

572
00:42:18,953 --> 00:42:20,412
She totally screwed you over.

573
00:42:21,413 --> 00:42:23,249
-Where's Nora?
-Who knows?

574
00:42:23,332 --> 00:42:24,875
That brat won't even answer my calls.

575
00:42:26,001 --> 00:42:28,671
What in the world happened
after I moved out?

576
00:42:33,008 --> 00:42:35,094
-In-ja.
-Yes, honey?

577
00:42:39,974 --> 00:42:41,183
Do you

578
00:42:41,976 --> 00:42:43,435
want to come with me?

579
00:42:44,937 --> 00:42:45,771
What?

580
00:43:34,111 --> 00:43:35,279
We've arrived, sir.

581
00:43:38,282 --> 00:43:39,116
Oh, right.

582
00:43:42,786 --> 00:43:44,705
Hey, where did she go?

583
00:43:45,456 --> 00:43:46,290
Hey!

584
00:43:47,041 --> 00:43:48,125
What in the world?

585
00:43:53,797 --> 00:43:54,757
What the…

586
00:43:55,507 --> 00:43:56,342
You!

587
00:43:57,343 --> 00:43:58,177
You're…

588
00:43:59,094 --> 00:44:00,304
A NEW POLICE FORCE COMMITTED TO THE PEOPLE

589
00:44:00,387 --> 00:44:01,764
Wait a minute.

590
00:44:01,847 --> 00:44:03,641
What's going on here?

591
00:44:05,059 --> 00:44:06,101
Choi In-ja!

592
00:44:06,185 --> 00:44:07,269
What?

593
00:44:07,353 --> 00:44:08,479
Why are you calling me?

594
00:44:09,647 --> 00:44:12,483
Mr. Kang Pil-beom,
I'm a former Miss Korea.

595
00:44:12,566 --> 00:44:15,653
The one-time Best New Actress nominee
at the Golden Dragon Film Awards,

596
00:44:15,736 --> 00:44:16,987
Choi In-ja.

597
00:44:17,071 --> 00:44:18,322
I'm not the kind of woman

598
00:44:18,405 --> 00:44:20,491
who'd live in fear,
hiding out with a fugitive.

599
00:44:47,559 --> 00:44:49,645
-Hey.
-The chairman asked you for his passport

600
00:44:49,728 --> 00:44:51,063
and his emergency cash, right?

601
00:44:51,146 --> 00:44:53,273
I found the passport and cash.

602
00:44:53,357 --> 00:44:54,274
And the plane ticket?

603
00:44:54,358 --> 00:44:57,736
Tell him the flight departs
from Kimpo Airport at 11 p.m. tonight

604
00:44:57,820 --> 00:44:59,571
and that you'll pick up the tickets there.

605
00:44:59,655 --> 00:45:01,990
Departing from Kimpo Airport
at 11 p.m. tonight.

606
00:45:02,074 --> 00:45:02,908
Got it.

607
00:45:02,991 --> 00:45:05,577
Your final destination
will be the police station.

608
00:45:07,746 --> 00:45:09,873
Babe, I got this.

609
00:45:13,627 --> 00:45:14,962
Choi In-ja!

610
00:45:16,547 --> 00:45:17,506
Why you…

611
00:45:21,301 --> 00:45:22,219
Damn it!

612
00:45:25,889 --> 00:45:27,224
-Chairman Kang Pil-beom.
-Let go!

613
00:45:27,307 --> 00:45:28,600
We'd appreciate your cooperation.

614
00:45:29,184 --> 00:45:30,686
-My goodness.
-Let's go.

615
00:45:31,395 --> 00:45:32,646
I can't believe this.

616
00:45:33,689 --> 00:45:34,523
Let go of me!

617
00:45:37,443 --> 00:45:39,319
This is unbelievable.

618
00:45:43,073 --> 00:45:44,283
Thank you, ma'am.

619
00:45:46,034 --> 00:45:48,787
A man who makes you ashamed
that you ever lived with him

620
00:45:48,871 --> 00:45:50,372
deserves to face judgment.

621
00:46:01,967 --> 00:46:02,801
Come here.

622
00:46:21,904 --> 00:46:24,448
BONAK POLICE STATION

623
00:46:33,499 --> 00:46:34,500
Thank you.

624
00:46:34,583 --> 00:46:37,586
YUN JAE-UNG'S PERSONAL EFFECTS

625
00:46:59,566 --> 00:47:02,694
CHEONGSAN ACCOUNTING FIRM
YUN JAE-UNG

626
00:47:06,114 --> 00:47:08,200
RESIDENT REGISTRATION CARD
YUN JAE-UNG

627
00:47:51,410 --> 00:47:52,244
Today,

628
00:47:53,245 --> 00:47:56,331
I went to the places I used to go
with Uncle Myeong-hwi.

629
00:47:57,583 --> 00:47:59,918
The movie theater, record shop,

630
00:48:00,419 --> 00:48:01,920
basketball court, places like that.

631
00:48:03,630 --> 00:48:04,965
I wanted to commemorate him.

632
00:48:06,508 --> 00:48:07,342
Oh, right.

633
00:48:09,052 --> 00:48:10,637
I'm going to use his wallet now.

634
00:48:12,556 --> 00:48:14,641
I'm glad to see you holding up.

635
00:48:16,018 --> 00:48:19,521
Director Yun had a really tough day today.

636
00:48:20,564 --> 00:48:22,357
Learning his little brother's death

637
00:48:22,441 --> 00:48:24,192
wasn't a suicide but a homicide…

638
00:48:30,616 --> 00:48:32,117
So you called me to check in on me?

639
00:48:33,702 --> 00:48:34,620
But

640
00:48:34,703 --> 00:48:36,455
I'd rather live like this than live a lie.

641
00:48:37,914 --> 00:48:39,833
Uncle Myeong-hwi would want this for me.

642
00:48:44,212 --> 00:48:45,714
If it weren't for you,

643
00:48:46,423 --> 00:48:48,383
none of this would've been possible.

644
00:48:48,884 --> 00:48:50,052
Thank you.

645
00:48:51,637 --> 00:48:52,679
That thank you…

646
00:48:54,056 --> 00:48:55,682
sounds too much like a goodbye.

647
00:49:26,755 --> 00:49:27,673
You should go.

648
00:49:28,840 --> 00:49:30,550
I'm going to stay for a bit longer.

649
00:49:32,803 --> 00:49:33,679
Okay then.

650
00:49:53,031 --> 00:49:53,907
Goodbye…

651
00:49:55,909 --> 00:49:56,910
Hong Jang-mi.

652
00:50:04,126 --> 00:50:07,421
After the chairman was arrested,
customer complaints have only escalated.

653
00:50:07,504 --> 00:50:09,214
SET YOUR MIND AT EASE WITH HANMIN
NEW HIGH-YIELD INVESTMENT PRODUCT!

654
00:50:09,297 --> 00:50:12,259
The branch manager ran out yesterday
and never returned.

655
00:50:12,342 --> 00:50:13,760
He didn't come into work today.

656
00:50:14,845 --> 00:50:16,847
What if the company goes under?

657
00:50:16,930 --> 00:50:18,724
What are you doing, Ms. Kim?

658
00:50:19,349 --> 00:50:22,644
A few angry customers,
and this place will be a mess again.

659
00:50:23,145 --> 00:50:25,522
Yeah, I heard
even the head office has given up.

660
00:50:25,605 --> 00:50:26,857
We should still do our jobs.

661
00:50:27,983 --> 00:50:29,735
The company hasn't gone under yet.

662
00:50:35,073 --> 00:50:36,283
MS. KIM AT MAGANG BRANCH

663
00:50:36,366 --> 00:50:37,868
KIM MI-SOOK AT MAGANG BRANCH

664
00:50:38,994 --> 00:50:39,995
MS. LEE AT CHEONGAN BRANCH

665
00:50:40,078 --> 00:50:41,121
LEE HE-GYEONG AT CHEONGAN BRANCH

666
00:50:42,622 --> 00:50:43,457
MS. PARK AT BUKJEONGWON BRANCH

667
00:50:43,540 --> 00:50:44,958
PARK MYEONG-HUI AT BUKJEONGWON BRANCH

668
00:50:45,041 --> 00:50:46,251
MS. KIM AT BUKJEONGWON BRANCH

669
00:50:46,334 --> 00:50:48,211
KIM MI-GYEONG AT BUKJEONGWON BRANCH

670
00:50:49,296 --> 00:50:50,672
KIM HYEON-SUK AT YEONGPO BRANCH

671
00:50:50,756 --> 00:50:52,174
LEE GYEONG-SUK AT YEONGPO BRANCH

672
00:50:52,257 --> 00:50:54,259
<i>Kang Pil-beom,</i>
<i>the former chairman of Hanmin,</i>

673
00:50:54,342 --> 00:50:57,179
<i>who was indicted on charges</i>
<i>of embezzlement and breach of duty,</i>

674
00:50:57,262 --> 00:50:58,805
<i>was found guilty in his second trial.</i>

675
00:50:58,889 --> 00:51:02,309
<i>Kang expressed his intention</i>
<i>to file an immediate appeal.</i>

676
00:51:02,392 --> 00:51:04,102
<i>Meanwhile, Yeouido Pirates will be</i>

677
00:51:04,186 --> 00:51:07,355
<i>selling its shares to the Hanmin Employee</i>
<i>Stock Ownership Association.</i>

678
00:51:07,439 --> 00:51:10,609
This share sale is to foster
shared growth with employees

679
00:51:10,692 --> 00:51:12,277
while strengthening shareholder value.

680
00:51:12,360 --> 00:51:15,030
All slush funds amassed
by former Chairman Kang

681
00:51:15,113 --> 00:51:16,948
will be returned to Hanmin.

682
00:51:17,449 --> 00:51:22,162
And Yeouido Pirates will disband
after a new head of Hanmin is appointed.

683
00:51:30,837 --> 00:51:31,671
Mr. Cha.

684
00:51:31,755 --> 00:51:33,089
Why are you acting weird…

685
00:51:34,674 --> 00:51:36,092
Why are you delivering the coffee?

686
00:51:36,176 --> 00:51:37,052
Ms. Hong.

687
00:51:37,803 --> 00:51:39,221
Ms. Hong Keum-bo.

688
00:51:39,304 --> 00:51:41,306
That was a discriminatory comment.

689
00:51:41,932 --> 00:51:42,849
Me?

690
00:51:43,600 --> 00:51:45,977
I don't think I should be hearing that
from you, of all people.

691
00:51:49,022 --> 00:51:52,192
I'll leave you to your meeting then.

692
00:52:17,384 --> 00:52:18,927
To get straight to the point,

693
00:52:19,010 --> 00:52:21,096
many people in the company believe

694
00:52:21,179 --> 00:52:24,099
that you'd be the right choice
to lead Hanmin at this time.

695
00:52:25,600 --> 00:52:26,935
I can't do that.

696
00:52:27,561 --> 00:52:29,980
Given my involvement
in the creation of the slush fund,

697
00:52:30,522 --> 00:52:31,398
I'm not qualified.

698
00:52:33,358 --> 00:52:35,694
I'm sure there are

699
00:52:36,444 --> 00:52:39,114
many career executives eyeing the role.

700
00:52:39,197 --> 00:52:40,532
There certainly is a lot,

701
00:52:41,116 --> 00:52:43,743
but there's a strong backlash
after the DK Ventures incident.

702
00:52:50,834 --> 00:52:53,253
Where could we possibly find
someone who understands

703
00:52:53,336 --> 00:52:55,380
Hanmin's current situation
with your financial acumen,

704
00:52:55,463 --> 00:52:57,966
leadership skills,
and even moral integrity?

705
00:53:08,560 --> 00:53:12,689
There is one person
who has delivered consistent results

706
00:53:12,772 --> 00:53:13,940
over a long tenure,

707
00:53:14,024 --> 00:53:17,569
and had only marginal involvement
in the former chairman's slush fund.

708
00:53:18,194 --> 00:53:20,488
He also possesses keen management skills,

709
00:53:20,572 --> 00:53:22,991
and I think he might be a good fit.

710
00:53:26,995 --> 00:53:29,039
I hope it's not who I think it is.

711
00:53:29,122 --> 00:53:32,584
Sometimes, the position makes the leader.

712
00:53:51,311 --> 00:53:52,520
I have three questions.

713
00:53:52,604 --> 00:53:54,773
Why did you help us
at the shareholders' meeting?

714
00:53:56,399 --> 00:53:57,567
Because I wanted to follow

715
00:53:57,651 --> 00:53:59,319
my heart and not my head.

716
00:54:01,154 --> 00:54:02,113
What are you saying?

717
00:54:05,116 --> 00:54:07,535
As soon as Hong Keum-bo
stepped up to fight,

718
00:54:07,619 --> 00:54:10,163
it was obvious
that she'd be fighting a losing battle.

719
00:54:11,581 --> 00:54:14,709
My head told me
to side with Chairman Kang,

720
00:54:14,793 --> 00:54:16,169
but my heart, for some reason…

721
00:54:19,464 --> 00:54:21,424
wanted Hong Keum-bo to win.

722
00:54:24,469 --> 00:54:25,303
Satisfied?

723
00:54:32,602 --> 00:54:34,354
It was political instinct.

724
00:54:35,063 --> 00:54:37,607
Do you think I got to where I am
by just sitting around?

725
00:54:39,734 --> 00:54:41,528
Is it true that you weren't

726
00:54:41,611 --> 00:54:43,655
directly involved
in the slush fund creation?

727
00:54:45,031 --> 00:54:47,492
From Myeong-hwi, Mr. So,
and even Mr. Bang…

728
00:54:47,575 --> 00:54:50,453
I was the one who got stabbed in the back!

729
00:54:55,333 --> 00:54:56,167
Last question.

730
00:54:56,710 --> 00:54:59,129
Would you be interested
in an 11-month interim CEO position?

731
00:54:59,713 --> 00:55:00,755
Interim…

732
00:55:03,675 --> 00:55:04,718
CEO?

733
00:55:04,801 --> 00:55:07,262
Of course, it won't be my decision alone.

734
00:55:08,555 --> 00:55:10,557
A quick refusal would be great.

735
00:55:10,640 --> 00:55:12,308
"The position makes the leader."

736
00:55:13,435 --> 00:55:14,436
Does it, really?

737
00:55:19,149 --> 00:55:19,983
CEO?

738
00:55:23,653 --> 00:55:24,571
Oh my.

739
00:55:24,654 --> 00:55:26,781
NOTICE OF APPOINTMENT

740
00:55:26,865 --> 00:55:27,699
POSITION: CEO

741
00:55:27,782 --> 00:55:29,325
NAME: CHA JUNG-IL

742
00:55:29,826 --> 00:55:32,120
HANMIN INVESTMENT &amp; SECURITIES

743
00:55:32,203 --> 00:55:35,623
Let's make the employee payroll account
our flagship product.

744
00:55:35,707 --> 00:55:38,126
Let's offer them interest as banks do.

745
00:55:38,209 --> 00:55:40,587
We'll approach it
as comprehensive wealth management.

746
00:55:41,379 --> 00:55:44,924
I'd also like to see a campaign
targeting entry-level staff and new hires.

747
00:55:45,717 --> 00:55:48,720
This year's customer count is a bit--

748
00:55:49,304 --> 00:55:50,430
Hey!

749
00:55:58,104 --> 00:56:00,482
<i>"The position makes the leader."</i>

750
00:56:00,565 --> 00:56:01,524
<i>Does it, really?</i>

751
00:56:02,150 --> 00:56:03,109
<i>Ms. Hong.</i>

752
00:56:07,906 --> 00:56:10,116
Let's try to be more careful next time.

753
00:56:11,493 --> 00:56:13,203
Let's try…

754
00:56:13,703 --> 00:56:15,789
to make sure this doesn't happen again.

755
00:56:18,291 --> 00:56:19,125
You may leave.

756
00:56:19,209 --> 00:56:20,668
"THE POSITION MAKES THE LEADER…
DOES IT, REALLY?"

757
00:56:20,752 --> 00:56:23,421
"THE POSITION MADE THE LEADER!"
CHA JUNG-IL

758
00:56:59,290 --> 00:57:01,918
I'm here
for a lunch appointment with Nora.

759
00:57:02,752 --> 00:57:03,795
So am I.

760
00:57:06,506 --> 00:57:07,924
You haven't figured it out yet?

761
00:57:08,007 --> 00:57:10,552
She clearly set this up so we could meet.

762
00:57:24,399 --> 00:57:27,026
Ms. Kang Nora ordered it
when she made the reservation.

763
00:57:41,791 --> 00:57:43,877
Cha Jung-il becoming
the president of Hanmin?

764
00:57:46,045 --> 00:57:47,213
He won by luck.

765
00:57:47,297 --> 00:57:48,131
Dad.

766
00:57:48,798 --> 00:57:50,675
You still want it
after everything that happened?

767
00:57:52,218 --> 00:57:54,637
Son, if everyone grew from experience,

768
00:57:54,721 --> 00:57:56,389
this world would be full of saints.

769
00:58:12,322 --> 00:58:13,656
The steak is good.

770
00:58:20,413 --> 00:58:21,539
Open up.

771
00:58:29,172 --> 00:58:30,715
This steak is good indeed.

772
00:58:37,388 --> 00:58:38,765
The thing with money is…

773
00:58:40,099 --> 00:58:41,726
Never mind. Let's eat.

774
00:58:44,062 --> 00:58:45,980
ULLALA CHICKEN

775
00:58:46,064 --> 00:58:47,774
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

776
00:58:48,358 --> 00:58:50,068
Cheers, Ms. Go!

777
00:58:50,151 --> 00:58:51,486
DETAINED IN THE END!
CURRENTLY IN PRISON

778
00:58:54,739 --> 00:58:56,533
How's your new place, Big Al and Mr. Lee?

779
00:58:56,616 --> 00:58:58,910
It's a rooftop apartment,
so it has a nice view.

780
00:59:00,078 --> 00:59:02,121
You have enough money for a decent place.

781
00:59:02,205 --> 00:59:03,915
Big Al, you received your dividends,

782
00:59:03,998 --> 00:59:05,375
and Mr. Lee, you got your severance pay.

783
00:59:05,458 --> 00:59:08,378
I drained my savings to buy
my favorite video rental place.

784
00:59:08,461 --> 00:59:10,046
That screenplay I've been putting off…

785
00:59:10,880 --> 00:59:12,257
It's time to give it a final scene.

786
00:59:13,925 --> 00:59:16,010
I also started a game company.

787
00:59:16,594 --> 00:59:18,429
And I used up my severance to buy land.

788
00:59:18,513 --> 00:59:20,265
Am I the only one nervous about this?

789
00:59:20,348 --> 00:59:22,225
Where's the land?

790
00:59:23,184 --> 00:59:24,018
In Pangyo.

791
00:59:26,145 --> 00:59:29,232
It's mostly rice fields
and orchards right now,

792
00:59:29,315 --> 00:59:31,401
but just as Yeouido became
the center of finance,

793
00:59:31,484 --> 00:59:32,986
I'll grow my game company

794
00:59:33,069 --> 00:59:35,405
and turn that area into a leading IT hub!

795
00:59:40,618 --> 00:59:41,869
Good luck. Yeah.

796
00:59:41,953 --> 00:59:43,871
You never know what the future holds.

797
00:59:43,955 --> 00:59:45,915
Well, should we cheers to that?

798
00:59:47,333 --> 00:59:49,168
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

799
00:59:58,469 --> 01:00:00,138
ULLALA CHICKEN

800
01:00:00,221 --> 01:00:01,472
Your parents must be worried.

801
01:00:02,307 --> 01:00:03,141
It's fine.

802
01:00:03,850 --> 01:00:07,020
Compared to being fired from my first job
and living in exile at the library,

803
01:00:07,103 --> 01:00:09,272
I'm at least making a decent living now.

804
01:00:11,858 --> 01:00:13,735
I'm leaving Korea tomorrow.

805
01:00:15,361 --> 01:00:16,779
Why didn't you tell me sooner?

806
01:00:17,280 --> 01:00:18,489
You should at least say goodbye.

807
01:00:18,573 --> 01:00:21,075
I just didn't want it to be a farewell.

808
01:00:22,452 --> 01:00:23,828
You never know what the future holds.

809
01:00:27,165 --> 01:00:29,208
Thank you for all your hard work.

810
01:00:30,627 --> 01:00:33,254
It was my way of apologizing for the past,

811
01:00:33,338 --> 01:00:34,589
though I'm sure you already knew.

812
01:00:38,593 --> 01:00:40,345
I used to think

813
01:00:40,428 --> 01:00:43,389
fate and sincerity
were nothing but romantic excuses.

814
01:00:44,140 --> 01:00:47,727
But reuniting with you
and working alongside you

815
01:00:48,686 --> 01:00:49,979
gave those words meaning.

816
01:00:52,357 --> 01:00:53,524
Thank you for giving me

817
01:00:54,734 --> 01:00:55,735
a chance.

818
01:01:19,175 --> 01:01:20,510
JEONGBOM KINDERGARTEN GRADUATION

819
01:01:20,593 --> 01:01:21,928
FEBRUARY, 1999

820
01:01:22,011 --> 01:01:25,390
We will now present
the Cleaning Champion Award.

821
01:01:25,473 --> 01:01:27,100
Seo Won-jong!

822
01:01:29,435 --> 01:01:30,728
They're so cute.

823
01:01:32,647 --> 01:01:34,315
Who knew I'd end up
at a kindergarten graduation?

824
01:01:34,399 --> 01:01:35,274
I know, right?

825
01:01:36,275 --> 01:01:37,985
I present you with your award.

826
01:01:38,069 --> 01:01:40,279
-Congratulations.
-Thank you.

827
01:01:42,990 --> 01:01:44,867
Our Bom is all grown up now.

828
01:01:44,951 --> 01:01:46,411
She'll be in grade school in the spring.

829
01:01:46,494 --> 01:01:47,745
Elementary school.

830
01:01:48,287 --> 01:01:50,289
We should be celebrating, not criticizing.

831
01:01:50,373 --> 01:01:52,208
I only just got out of the slammer.

832
01:01:52,709 --> 01:01:53,960
I'll cut you slack this time.

833
01:01:54,544 --> 01:01:56,546
Wait, am I the only one with flowers?

834
01:01:56,629 --> 01:01:58,965
I made Bom's favorite dessert.

835
01:01:59,048 --> 01:02:00,133
Ta-da!

836
01:02:08,933 --> 01:02:11,936
<i>Auntie Nora went to France</i>
<i>to pursue her love for food</i>

837
01:02:12,019 --> 01:02:15,481
<i>and returned as a pastry chef.</i>

838
01:02:17,150 --> 01:02:18,484
I prepared cash.

839
01:02:18,568 --> 01:02:19,902
No muss, no fuss.

840
01:02:20,862 --> 01:02:22,655
<i>Big Auntie Bok-hee said</i>

841
01:02:22,739 --> 01:02:26,534
<i>she did just fine in prison,</i>
<i>managing backdoor money</i>

842
01:02:26,617 --> 01:02:29,495
<i>for inmates, guards, and even the warden.</i>

843
01:02:30,872 --> 01:02:33,291
<i>Now, she secretly operates</i>
<i>a private detective agency</i>

844
01:02:33,374 --> 01:02:35,501
<i>under the guise of a hair salon</i>

845
01:02:35,585 --> 01:02:38,379
<i>to help her clients find</i>
<i>their husbands' hidden slush funds.</i>

846
01:02:41,257 --> 01:02:42,175
Welcome.

847
01:02:42,258 --> 01:02:45,094
<i>She said the real Auntie Jang-mi</i>
<i>is her business partner.</i>

848
01:02:45,178 --> 01:02:47,597
-For women in their thirties--
-Twenties.

849
01:02:48,890 --> 01:02:50,391
-Sorry?
-I'm in my twenties.

850
01:02:51,642 --> 01:02:52,602
Can you do it?

851
01:02:52,685 --> 01:02:53,561
Sure.

852
01:02:55,354 --> 01:02:56,731
Who's looking to divorce?

853
01:02:56,814 --> 01:02:58,191
Me. That's me.

854
01:02:58,274 --> 01:02:59,901
Listen carefully.

855
01:02:59,984 --> 01:03:01,611
You must check if he's hiding any money

856
01:03:01,694 --> 01:03:05,281
before you throw
those divorce papers at your husband.

857
01:03:05,364 --> 01:03:07,450
Bank accounts,
insurance policies, and land deeds!

858
01:03:19,128 --> 01:03:21,214
This award goes
to everyone's greatest friend.

859
01:03:21,297 --> 01:03:23,382
The Friendship Award goes to

860
01:03:23,466 --> 01:03:24,425
Kim Bom!

861
01:03:28,012 --> 01:03:29,514
Way to go, Bom!

862
01:03:29,597 --> 01:03:30,890
So cool, Bom!

863
01:03:30,973 --> 01:03:32,517
So cute, Bom!

864
01:03:34,435 --> 01:03:35,603
The Friendship Award

865
01:03:35,686 --> 01:03:38,231
is awarded to everyone's greatest friend,
Kim Bom.

866
01:03:38,815 --> 01:03:39,732
Congratulations.

867
01:03:50,159 --> 01:03:51,494
Hey, Mom!

868
01:03:52,578 --> 01:03:55,832
<i>As for my mom, Ms. Kim Mi-sook…</i>

869
01:03:55,915 --> 01:03:58,709
This is so damn annoying.

870
01:03:58,793 --> 01:04:00,586
I told you that's what I want.

871
01:04:00,670 --> 01:04:03,297
Who are you to tell me no?
Is this your money?

872
01:04:03,381 --> 01:04:04,382
Is it?

873
01:04:08,052 --> 01:04:09,387
Who the hell are you to--

874
01:04:13,850 --> 01:04:14,684
Sir.

875
01:04:14,767 --> 01:04:16,310
Please refrain
from using abusive language.

876
01:04:17,061 --> 01:04:19,480
What? Who are you?

877
01:04:20,064 --> 01:04:23,234
If you continue to cause fear,
I will report you to the police.

878
01:04:28,406 --> 01:04:30,199
<i>She attends an online university</i>

879
01:04:30,283 --> 01:04:32,952
<i>and still works at Hanmin,</i>

880
01:04:33,035 --> 01:04:35,329
<i>now as an assistant manager.</i>

881
01:04:48,259 --> 01:04:49,552
<i>This dormitory</i>

882
01:04:49,635 --> 01:04:52,680
<i>will officially cease operations</i>
<i>on February 8, 1999.</i>

883
01:04:52,763 --> 01:04:55,850
<i>We thank all residents</i>
<i>from the bottom of our hearts,</i>

884
01:04:55,933 --> 01:04:58,769
<i>and we sincerely wish you all</i>
<i>health and luck</i>

885
01:04:58,853 --> 01:05:00,313
<i>throughout the four seasons.</i>

886
01:05:00,396 --> 01:05:02,356
They must've already moved everything out.

887
01:05:02,440 --> 01:05:04,984
Too bad, I wanted to look inside.

888
01:05:05,067 --> 01:05:07,486
I'm sure the RA would
give us permission if we asked.

889
01:05:08,696 --> 01:05:10,489
Should I ask the security guard?

890
01:05:12,575 --> 01:05:15,119
We know the gate
isn't the only way inside.

891
01:05:46,192 --> 01:05:47,401
Are you okay?

892
01:05:47,485 --> 01:05:49,195
Let's go. Come on.

893
01:05:55,660 --> 01:05:58,079
Gosh, these halls feel so empty now.

894
01:06:35,282 --> 01:06:37,535
It's nice to meet you. I'm Hong Jang-mi.

895
01:06:38,619 --> 01:06:40,204
I turned 20

896
01:06:40,788 --> 01:06:41,747
this year.

897
01:06:42,915 --> 01:06:43,749
Here.

898
01:06:43,833 --> 01:06:44,792
Hong Jang-mi.

899
01:06:44,875 --> 01:06:48,504
As of today, you're officially recognized
as a resident of Room 301.

900
01:06:49,714 --> 01:06:50,715
Thanks.

901
01:06:50,798 --> 01:06:53,426
Gather around, Room 301.

902
01:06:53,509 --> 01:06:54,552
Ta-da.

903
01:06:54,635 --> 01:06:56,178
Living under the same roof

904
01:06:56,262 --> 01:06:58,472
and sharing meals makes us family.

905
01:07:04,895 --> 01:07:06,313
Operation Seodongyo is a go.

906
01:07:06,397 --> 01:07:07,523
Help me out, ladies.

907
01:07:08,441 --> 01:07:10,651
FEMALE EMPLOYEE… FIRED… HONG JANG-MI…

908
01:07:10,735 --> 01:07:12,153
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

909
01:07:18,993 --> 01:07:20,244
Mommy.

910
01:07:28,669 --> 01:07:30,171
Good job!

911
01:07:30,254 --> 01:07:31,589
Ta-da.

912
01:07:32,089 --> 01:07:33,466
What are beeper numbers?

913
01:07:33,549 --> 01:07:36,594
If you're ever in trouble,
you just need to call one of the aunties.

914
01:07:37,178 --> 01:07:39,221
We're Bom's aunties!

915
01:07:39,305 --> 01:07:40,181
Bom.

916
01:07:44,977 --> 01:07:46,937
What are we going to do?

917
01:07:50,816 --> 01:07:52,443
Are you okay? Are you hurt anywhere?

918
01:07:52,526 --> 01:07:53,778
Tell me you're okay first!

919
01:07:53,861 --> 01:07:54,779
I'm fine.

920
01:07:57,281 --> 01:07:59,325
I thought you'd be worried
about the money,

921
01:07:59,408 --> 01:08:01,077
but you worried about me first.

922
01:08:01,160 --> 01:08:02,286
Seriously?

923
01:08:02,995 --> 01:08:04,914
You can call her big sis.

924
01:08:04,997 --> 01:08:06,624
Everyone knows she's old.

925
01:08:09,085 --> 01:08:10,127
Mommy!

926
01:08:10,211 --> 01:08:11,212
Bom!

927
01:08:13,255 --> 01:08:14,757
Bom, I'm so sorry.

928
01:08:28,187 --> 01:08:30,648
Let's all take a picture together.

929
01:08:46,831 --> 01:08:49,291
<i>It is the Year of the White Metal Dragon.</i>

930
01:08:49,375 --> 01:08:52,837
<i>The dragon has long been</i>
<i>a symbol of great hope and success,</i>

931
01:08:52,920 --> 01:08:56,382
<i>and there is understandably great hope</i>
<i>for the year ahead.</i>

932
01:08:56,465 --> 01:09:00,136
<i>Leaders worldwide have shared messages</i>
<i>to commemorate the millennium,</i>

933
01:09:00,219 --> 01:09:04,056
<i>stressing the importance</i>
<i>of global cooperation and progress.</i>

934
01:09:08,102 --> 01:09:09,770
Winning the reinstatement case

935
01:09:11,063 --> 01:09:12,439
won't be easy.

936
01:09:12,523 --> 01:09:15,192
Will you start the new millennium
on a sour note?

937
01:09:15,276 --> 01:09:16,360
However…

938
01:09:18,946 --> 01:09:21,615
I'm considering proposing
a conditional reinstatement.

939
01:09:23,534 --> 01:09:26,203
It appears you're here
to represent the organization.

940
01:09:27,329 --> 01:09:28,289
Fine, I'll play along.

941
01:09:30,457 --> 01:09:33,127
This reinstatement lawsuit
seeks formal recognition

942
01:09:33,210 --> 01:09:35,421
of my employee status
during my undercover work in 1997.

943
01:09:35,504 --> 01:09:37,298
I do not wish to negotiate it as a term.

944
01:09:38,924 --> 01:09:40,217
Why the sudden business tone?

945
01:09:41,343 --> 01:09:43,220
You said you wanted to come back, Hong.

946
01:09:43,304 --> 01:09:46,473
I'm trying to justify that
for both you and the organization.

947
01:09:49,059 --> 01:09:50,227
I'll hear you out for now.

948
01:09:58,235 --> 01:10:01,280
These bodies were found along highways
and in the hills in South Gyeongsang.

949
01:10:01,363 --> 01:10:02,531
VICTIM 1: PARK MI-JEONG
YOU &amp; ME INSURANCE AGENT

950
01:10:02,615 --> 01:10:05,868
The police are treating it
as a serial murder case for now.

951
01:10:05,951 --> 01:10:07,036
But the thing is,

952
01:10:07,119 --> 01:10:10,080
all of the victims
have one thing in common.

953
01:10:11,290 --> 01:10:12,208
Insurance.

954
01:10:13,000 --> 01:10:14,084
Insurance.

955
01:10:15,586 --> 01:10:17,004
Two insurance agents,

956
01:10:17,087 --> 01:10:19,089
an insurance policyholder,

957
01:10:19,173 --> 01:10:20,591
and a beneficiary.

958
01:10:20,674 --> 01:10:23,135
They're all through You &amp; Me Insurance.

959
01:10:23,219 --> 01:10:26,680
They were also supposed to testify for us
in the insurance fraud case.

960
01:10:30,476 --> 01:10:31,393
So?

961
01:10:31,936 --> 01:10:36,065
Would you go undercover again
and help carry out the investigation?

962
01:10:37,942 --> 01:10:39,151
Again?

963
01:10:39,235 --> 01:10:40,819
You want me to do that nonsense again?

964
01:10:40,903 --> 01:10:43,572
"Nonsense"? Come on now.

965
01:10:43,656 --> 01:10:46,200
You did great,
and you'll do great again this time.

966
01:10:46,700 --> 01:10:48,577
Let's put your skills to use again.

967
01:10:48,661 --> 01:10:50,329
It'll be just for three months.

968
01:10:50,412 --> 01:10:53,415
You don't have to worry about
appearances this time.

969
01:10:53,499 --> 01:10:56,752
Going undercover as a 20-year-old
last time was ridiculous.

970
01:10:57,336 --> 01:10:58,295
This time,

971
01:10:58,379 --> 01:11:01,090
you can be a 36-year-old
insurance agent or…

972
01:11:01,173 --> 01:11:02,841
Anyway, you've got many options.

973
01:11:02,925 --> 01:11:04,009
If you do well,

974
01:11:04,093 --> 01:11:06,512
you can choose the division you want
at the head office.

975
01:11:07,388 --> 01:11:09,974
The governor said whatever you want!

976
01:11:15,062 --> 01:11:15,980
But why me?

977
01:11:24,697 --> 01:11:27,074
That doesn't suit you at all.

978
01:11:29,702 --> 01:11:31,120
What about this?

979
01:11:31,203 --> 01:11:32,454
Sure. Knock yourself out.

980
01:11:33,747 --> 01:11:35,541
I need to look intimidating.

981
01:11:37,126 --> 01:11:38,377
Hong Keum-bo.

982
01:11:38,460 --> 01:11:41,255
Forget all the trouble,
and join me on a trip to LA.

983
01:11:42,131 --> 01:11:44,425
Queen Bee, I'm going to borrow this too.

984
01:11:44,508 --> 01:11:46,760
At least tell me
what kind of business trip it is.

985
01:11:47,845 --> 01:11:49,305
Visit me in Busan sometime.

986
01:11:49,388 --> 01:11:50,723
We can go to Gwangalli together.

987
01:11:51,307 --> 01:11:52,182
Busan?

988
01:11:53,600 --> 01:11:54,518
Gwangalli?

989
01:11:56,478 --> 01:12:00,482
GWANGALLI

990
01:12:00,566 --> 01:12:01,900
YOU &amp; ME INSURANCE
WILL TAKE FULL RESPONSIBILITY

991
01:12:19,752 --> 01:12:22,755
A certified black belt in martial arts,
a young male police officer,

992
01:12:22,838 --> 01:12:24,506
and two robust male employees

993
01:12:25,257 --> 01:12:26,592
were all knocked out.

994
01:12:27,551 --> 01:12:28,469
Hong,

995
01:12:29,178 --> 01:12:30,804
win the battle of nerves first.

996
01:12:31,347 --> 01:12:32,806
You know those ladies have some nerve.

997
01:12:35,434 --> 01:12:36,352
You got this!

998
01:12:57,956 --> 01:12:59,458
But you know,

999
01:12:59,541 --> 01:13:01,877
I really thought you'd get it.

1000
01:13:01,960 --> 01:13:04,380
I thought so too.

1001
01:13:04,463 --> 01:13:05,714
This year is a bust.

1002
01:13:06,757 --> 01:13:09,176
Bust? Do you know how much
she made in bonuses this month?

1003
01:13:09,259 --> 01:13:11,095
Yeah, that's right.

1004
01:13:11,595 --> 01:13:13,931
-As if I wouldn't know.
-Hold on a second.

1005
01:13:14,014 --> 01:13:18,060
I hear the new branch manager
is coming from the Seoul head office.

1006
01:13:18,143 --> 01:13:19,645
-She's a Seoulite?
-Yeah.

1007
01:13:20,646 --> 01:13:22,564
She's probably some frail little thing.

1008
01:13:22,648 --> 01:13:24,900
-Like me?
-Stop it already.

1009
01:13:24,983 --> 01:13:27,027
You should make that into a package.

1010
01:13:27,111 --> 01:13:28,904
Listen, you…

1011
01:13:29,571 --> 01:13:31,532
-Stop it.
-You're unbelievable.

1012
01:13:35,452 --> 01:13:36,620
What's your deal, kid?

1013
01:13:36,703 --> 01:13:37,955
She might not be a kid.

1014
01:13:40,249 --> 01:13:42,918
Hello, I'm Hong Keum-bo.

1015
01:13:43,001 --> 01:13:43,836
I'm…

1016
01:13:45,796 --> 01:13:47,589
the new bookkeeper here.

1017
01:13:50,134 --> 01:13:51,552
Gosh, you scared us!

1018
01:13:52,261 --> 01:13:53,679
Come here.

1019
01:13:53,762 --> 01:13:56,056
You're the new bookkeeper?
It's nice to meet you.

1020
01:13:57,099 --> 01:14:00,644
My goodness, I thought…

1021
01:14:03,063 --> 01:14:05,315
I look forward to working with you.

1022
01:14:07,651 --> 01:14:09,528
You are such a pretty young lady!

1023
01:14:20,539 --> 01:14:24,585
UNDERCOVER MISS HONG

1024
01:14:25,627 --> 01:14:27,463
UNDERCOVER MISS HONG

1025
01:14:27,963 --> 01:14:31,758
SPECIAL THANKS TO SHIN YU-NA
AND PARK JUNG-PYO FOR THEIR APPEARANCES

1026
01:14:31,842 --> 01:14:35,262
Hanmin is, in name and reality,
a first-rate company that has led…

1027
